09-10 March - Indian Summer Bake 

- 4 tablespoon olive oil
- 2 large potatoes (3/4 lb each), skin left on
- 2 zucchini, 1/2 lb each
- 3 ripe tomatoes (1 lb total)
- 3 cloves garlic
- Coarse salt, to taste
- Coarsely ground black pepper to taste
- 1/2 cup chopped fresh parsley
- Finely grated zest of 1 lemon

Preheat oven to 375F. Lightly grease a 9x13" shallow pan with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Cut potatoes, zucchini, and tomatoes into very thin slices crosswise. Coarsely chop garlic. Lay sliced potatoes on bottom of pan overlapping slices by half. Drizzle with 1 tablespoon olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover potatoes with zucchini slices, drizzle with oil and sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic and 1/4 cup parsley and the lemon zest. Cover zucchini with tomato slices, the remaining olive oil, pepper and parsley. Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are tender when pierced with the tip of a knife. Serve hot or at room temperature. 